<br>
Here's the idea:<br>
<br>
Either INSTEAD of, or perhaps synchronous with, faction (Can you say algorithmic nightmare?), your alignment affects how NPC's deal with you.  Meaning...say you screw up your faction pretty badly with so and so...and there are only limited faction options for repair...you could just do all sorts of good @#$% that will bring up your &quot;alignment&quot;, causing your faction to be less of a problem.<br>
<br>
I suggest this because there are pitifully few ways to raise your faction with certain groups, and many of these ways cannot be utilized once faction with those groups are already in the toilet, thus de facto making the faction irrecoverable.<br>
<br>
Yes, I realize I made my own bed and now I'm laying in it, but it would be nice to give some RP options to getting back on the &quot;good side of the law&quot;...<br>
<br>
And, this &quot;low population&quot; server stuff I'm going to have to say is partial BS...How many of you have your server listing based on population instead of server name?  Is Firiona Vie in the top 10?  And WHO is telling you that they're gonna get rid of the server because of low population?  Somebody's smokin' stones.<br>
<br>
One of the benefits to Verant about taking down the actual server populations is now they have another convenient lie to tell us as to why they are too lazy to provide quality entertainment for our money.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong;  I must think it's worth it because I am still here.  But make no mistake, I think Verant is lying  to us because RP'ers are some of the most cranky, vocal, LITERATE pains-in-the-A@#$es they've ever seen and they are handling us using what I call the &quot;Nice Doggie&quot; technique, while they take our money.<br>
<br>
&quot;Diplomacy is saying 'Nice Doggie' until you can find a rock.&quot;<br>
-W. Rogers<br>
<br>
That being said, I'm for anything that gives an XP bonus, and a group of similarly-aligned people getting a bonus because they are all Good and fighting Evil, or all Evil fighting Good, would at least encourage the illusion of Roleplay...which, honestly, is what I'd shoot for, since this whole world is an illusion anyhow.  Even the Lewt D00ds will fall into line, because there is a tangible benefit to following the rules.  Nobody wants to take an experience penalty, even if it isn't really a PENALTY per se...merely a lack of bonus.  As you may well know, d00ds want every advantage...twinking, etc.<br>
<br>
The alignment bonus idea is pretty *$!#@ing smart.  If we can't turn d00ds into Roleplayers, we can at least make it to their (and consequently OUR) advantage to at least PRETEND they are.<br>
<br>
All right, I've rambled enough.  I don't know what to do about this server.  I love it more than any other Verant has to offer.  I despise the Lewt D00ds, but think that the Bazaar is the neatest thing since Medeco(R) locks, despite the lag.  So I guess I am somewhat of a hypocrite.  So take my opinion for what you think it is worth and not a bit more.<br>
<br>
<br>
